title: For Sale:   WWI Imperial Luger c.1915
postcontent:
This is an almost completely matching, 1915 Dated, DWM (Deutsche Waffen und Munitions Fabriken) WWI Imperial Luger. Only the magazines are non-matching. It is chambered for 9mm and has a standard 4" (100mm) barrel, fixed sights and walnut grips. The serial number appears on the front of the frame, on the left side of the receiver, on the side plate sear and trigger. The 1914 Model Luger is characterized by the short frame, the rear "V" cut fixed and front dovetailed sight, and the frame with the stock lug. It was produced from 1914 until 1918 for the German Military. 

The right side of the receiver displays all the Imperial Army acceptance stamps. Original grips are finely cut diamond shaped checkering made from walnut or in some cases beech wood. These grips are serial numbered to the gun. The inside of the gun is clean and well cared for. The exterior shows honest wear on the muzzle, barrel and high points on the sides. The barrel is shiny and shows distinct lands and grooves. This Luger shows characteristic holster wear on the side plate and front exposed edges of the rails and end of the barrel. I would rate it about 80% original finish. 

The Luger is accompanied by three magazines and a WWII issue holster with German military markings.

title: For Sale:  Astra 400 Pistol with Numbers Matching Holster & Ammo
postcontent:
This is a very nice Astra 400 semi-auto pistol made in Spain and chambered in the powerful 9mm Largo round. 

Pistol is date stamped with the letter I signifying that it was made in 1936 which is the year that the Spanish Civil War started. So it's quite likely that this pistol saw service in that war since it was a primary sidearm for both sides. 

Pistol is in very good to excellent condition with 90%+ of it's original blue metal finish. The grips are also in excellent shape with no cracks or chips. Bore is very good with no rust or pitting. All numbers match - lower frame, slide & barrel. 

The Astra 400 is an interesting, and unique pistol as it is able to chamber and safely fire a number of rounds including .38 ACP, 9mm Steyr, 9mm Browning Long and of course it's intended chambering - the 9mm Largo. There are also numerous reports of folks successfully shooting the standard 9mm Luger round although it's not a good practice because the shorter case length can cause head spacing issues.  

It should also be noted that the modern .38 Super and the Winchester 9x23 rounds will chamber and fire, however it unsafe to do so because these two cartridges operate at much higher pressures than this Astra was designed to handle. 

Another very unique feature is that this pistol comes with it's original issue holster which is ink stamped with the serial number of the pistol. I've collected military firearms for almost 37 years and can tell you that it's very unusual to see any pistol still with it's original holster almost 77 years after production. 

Pistol comes with it's original matching holster & shoulder strap, 3 original magazines, and 6 boxes (150 rounds) of Spanish Santa Barbara, brass case, non-corrosive hard ball ammo.  

Asking Price is $550 with pickup in the Brandon area. Buyer must be a Florida resident and at least 21 years old. 

Thanks for looking.
